				 Bail plea by Idris rejected
 OUR LEGAL REPORTER																								The chief metropolitan magistrate on Wednesday rejected Idris Alis bail plea and remanded him in judicial custody till December 5.																								The All India Minority Forum president was arrested last Saturday in connection with the Park Circus violence and has been charged with attempt to murder, rioting, causing injury to police and public and damaging public property.																								Ali will be produced in Sealdah court, where he is facing similar charges in another case, on Thursday.																								Alis lawyer Shahid Imam argued that his client was not a party to any conspiracy to spread violence in the city. He courted arrest while taking part in a peaceful demonstration at the Park Circus seven-point crossing on Wednesday morning.																								Ali, a lawyer, was at Calcutta High Court while the Park Circus area was being rocked by violence later in the day, Imam submitted.																								The public prosecutor opposed the bail plea.																								Several lawyers from the high court were present in Bankshal court while Alis bail plea was being heard. Alis elder son Imran has written to the Bar Association of Calcutta High Court, seeking support for his father.
